Write a list of chapters for a report on "Tactical and Strategic Management Objectives". The list of chapters contains 6 paragraphs.

When writing the list of chapters, focus on the topic. you can use the following text:

Planning can be categorized according to several criteria:
- by degree of coverage (general and partial);
- by content in the aspect of entrepreneurial activity (strategic - search for new opportunities and products, tactical - prerequisites for known opportunities and products, operational - realization of the given opportunity);
- by the subject (object) of planning (target, means, potential, equipment, materials, finance, information, actions);
- by spheres of functioning (production, marketing, R&D, finance);
- by coverage (global, contour, macro, detailed);
- in terms of time (short-, medium-, long-term);
- by the degree of adaptability (rigid and flexible).

In the series of co-subordination of the firm's plans, the following types of planning are distinguished:
- general (long-term fundamental, the concept of the firm);
- strategic (long-term development of the firm, everyday life, production, R&D, personnel);
- tactical (conditions of economic operations - production facilities, means of production, capital, investments, personnel, etc.);
- operational planning (specific actions for a short-term period).

There are four main functions of managerial activity within the planning process: resource allocation, adaptation to the external environment, internal coordination
